# Echo Live desktop ‚Äî Vite environment files
#
# Vite loads files in this priority (later wins):
#   .env  ‚Üí  .env.<mode>  ‚Üí  .env.local  ‚Üí  .env.<mode>.local
#
# `<mode>` is `development` for `tauri dev`, `production` for `tauri build`.
# `.env.local` files are gitignored and load in EVERY mode ‚Äî keep nothing
# mode-specific there.
#
# File layout this project uses:
#
#   .env.production          ‚Üí committed prod defaults (Vercel + Convex)
#   .env.development.local   ‚Üí your gitignored dev overrides (e.g. ngrok)
#   .env.local               ‚Üí universal local overrides (e.g. a different
#                              Convex deployment for testing)
#
# Copy this file to `.env.development.local` and fill in:

# Convex deployment ‚Äî same value as packages/backend/.env.local
VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://bold-raccoon-845.convex.cloud
VITE_CONVEX_SITE_URL=https://bold-raccoon-845.convex.site

# Streaming infra for local dev (desktop pushes to local MediaMTX).
VITE_RTMP_HOST=rtmp://localhost:1935

# Phone-testing tunnel. Replace with your current ngrok URL or remove
# entirely to default to localhost:3000.
# VITE_HLS_HOST=https://<your-tunnel>.ngrok-free.dev/hls
# VITE_WEB_HOST=https://<your-tunnel>.ngrok-free.dev

# Optional: where the sign-in browser tab opens. Defaults to localhost in
# dev (avoids ngrok's interstitial) and to VITE_WEB_HOST in prod.
# VITE_AUTH_HOST=http://localhost:3000
